.TH LCS 8 "2026-05-11" "lcs 1.1.0" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
lcs \- command line client for the Lightweight Cluster Service daemon
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lcs
.RB [ \-s
.IR SOCKET | \-\-socket
.IR SOCKET ]
.B status
.br
.B lcs
.RB [ \-s
.IR SOCKET | \-\-socket
.IR SOCKET ]
.B nrpe
.br
.B lcs
.RB [ \-s
.IR SOCKET | \-\-socket
.IR SOCKET ]
.B resource
.B list
.br
.B lcs
.RB [ \-s
.IR SOCKET | \-\-socket
.IR SOCKET ]
.B resource
.B move
.I RESOURCE
.I NODE
.br
.B lcs
.RB [ \-s
.IR SOCKET | \-\-socket
.IR SOCKET ]
.B resource
.B start
.I RESOURCE
.br
.B lcs
.RB [ \-s
.IR SOCKET | \-\-socket
.IR SOCKET ]
.B resource
.B stop
.I RESOURCE
.br
.B lcs
.RB [ \-s
.IR SOCKET | \-\-socket
.IR SOCKET ]
.B resource
.B clear-conflict
.I RESOURCE
.br
.B lcs
.B \-\-version
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B lcs
talks to the local
.BR lcsd (8)
daemon over its Unix domain socket. It does not connect directly to remote
cluster nodes.
.PP
The tool is intended for querying cluster state, performing controlled VIP
handoffs, clearing inspected conflict states, and producing simple monitoring
output.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-s " SOCKET" "\fR, \fB\-\-socket " SOCKET
Connect to the given local daemon socket instead of the default
.IR /run/lcs/lcsd.sock .
.TP
.B \-\-version
Print the program version and exit.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Print usage information and exit.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B status
Print cluster quorum, node, and VIP state as seen by the local daemon. The
cluster section includes the current membership shape duration.
.TP
.B nrpe
Print a single monitoring-plugin style status line and exit with Nagios
compatible status codes. Exit status is 0 for OK, 1 for WARNING, 2 for
CRITICAL, and 3 for UNKNOWN.
.TP
.B resource list
Print a compact resource-only view.
.TP
.BI resource " move RESOURCE NODE"
Request a controlled cluster-level move of
.I RESOURCE
to
.IR NODE .
The old owner is asked to release the VIP, the cluster records a newer lease
epoch, and the target activates the VIP only after it obtains a majority lease.
For keep-together groups, moving a lower-priority member may be redirected to
the highest-priority group member so the whole group moves consistently.
Moving a VIP away from its configured home node blocks automatic return until
a later manual move back to that home node succeeds.
.TP
.BI resource " start RESOURCE"
Clear an administrative stop and allow normal placement to start
.IR RESOURCE .
.TP
.BI resource " stop RESOURCE"
Administratively stop
.I RESOURCE
in cluster memory and release it through the normal stop path, including hooks.
The stop is not persisted across a full cluster restart.
.TP
.BI resource " clear-conflict RESOURCE"
Clear the conflict state for
.I RESOURCE
after an administrator has inspected and resolved the underlying IP conflict.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Show local cluster status:
.EX
lcs status
.EE
.TP
Query a non-default daemon socket:
.EX
lcs -s /tmp/lcs-node1.sock status
.EE
.TP
Move a VIP to another full-member node:
.EX
lcs resource move vip1 node2
.EE
.TP
Temporarily stop and start a resource:
.EX
lcs resource stop vip1
lcs resource start vip1
.EE
.TP
Run a monitoring check:
.EX
lcs nrpe
.EE
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /run/lcs/lcsd.sock
Default local daemon control socket.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR lcsd (8)
